SELINUX ENABLE/DISABLE SCRIPT DOCUMENTATION
===========================================

1. OVERVIEW
-----------
These scripts are used to manage the SELinux operating mode on a Linux system by modifying the persistent configuration file located at:

/etc/selinux/config

The scripts automate:
- Backing up the existing SELinux configuration
- Updating SELINUX= and SELINUXTYPE= values
- Displaying the updated configuration
- Reminding the user that a system reboot is required for changes to take effect

SELinux modes:
- enforcing  : SELinux actively enforces policies
- permissive : SELinux logs policy violations but does not enforce them
- disabled   : SELinux is completely turned off (requires reboot)

These scripts modify the persistent configuration only. The system must be rebooted for changes to apply.


